      "gain": "proportional|weak|excessive|zero",
      "delay": "short|moderate|excessive",
      "description": "what this loop regulates or drives"
    }
  ],
  "effort_hotspots": [
    {
      "location": "where effort concentrates",
      "element": "which decomposed element it maps to",
      "effort_level": "high|medium|low",
      "value_produced": "what value this effort generates",
      "recommendation": "reduce|redirect|maintain"
    }
  ],
  "loop_health_summary": "Overall assessment of loop health across the system"
}
```

## Constraints

- Every effort hotspot must map to an element from the decomposed layers (Phase 1).
- Broken loops (closure = broken) must be flagged prominently — they represent wasted effort.
- The loop health summary should inform Phase 3: broken loops and low-value hotspots are prime reduction candidates.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

